The paper deals with topics related to computational geometry, such as planar graphs, straight-line embeddings, and order types, which are typically studied in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of a computer program to enumerate universal point sets suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), while the impossibility result for n-universal point sets may be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The study of planar graphs and their embeddings also has connections to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
